x4freetext: 4PI HALPERN-TYPE NEUTRON DETECTOR.
NATURAL (VIRTUALLY MONO-ISOTOPIC:  PR-141 ABUNDANCE IS
NEAR 100 PERCENTS,  THAT OF LA-139 - 99.91  PERCENTS)
TARGETS OF LA AND PR METALS WERE USED.
THE VARIABLE-BIN PENFOLD-LEISS UNFOLDING METHOD
WAS USED   FOR  OBTAINING  CROSS  SECTION  DATA  FROM
EXPERIMENTAL YIELD CURVE.
MEAN ROOT-SQUARE ERRORS ARE GIVEN.
THE DATA HAVE BEEN DIGITIZED IN USA LLNL AND
OBTAINED BY CDFE IN THE FORM OF DATA TABLES.
THE (G,XN) = ((G,N) + (G,NP) + 2(G,2N) +... ) REACTION
CROSS SECTION WAS OBTAINED.  THE THRESHOLD  OF (G,NP)
REACTION IS 14.4 MEV, THAT FOR (G,2N) - 17.3 MEV.
